user_query: Plot employee distribution by department
sql_query:
SELECT /*+ MAX_EXECUTION_TIME(30000) */ 
    e.first_name,
    e.last_name,
    d.name AS department_name,
    COUNT(p.id) AS num_projects,
    SUM(e.salary * 1.0 / (12 * 4)) AS avg_salary_per_month
FROM 
    employe e
JOIN 
    departments d ON e.department_id = d.id
LEFT JOIN 
    employee_projects ep ON e.id = ep.employee_id
LEFT JOIN 
    projects p ON ep.project_id = p.id
GROUP BY 
    e.first_name, e.last_name, d.name
ORDER BY 
    num_projects DESC, avg_salary_per_month DESC
LIMIT 10;

user_query: Which department has the highest paid employees and show the breakdown
sql_query:
SELECT /*+ MAX_EXECUTION_TIME(30000) */ 
    d.name AS department_name,
    COUNT(e.id) as total_employees,
    AVG(p.hours_worked) as avg_hours_worked,
    MAX(p.hours_worked) as max_hours_worked,
    MIN(p.hours_worked) as min_hours_worked
FROM 
    employe e
JOIN 
    departments d ON e.department_id = d.id
LEFT JOIN 
    performance p ON e.id = p.employee_id
GROUP BY 
    d.name
ORDER BY 
    total_employees DESC
LIMIT 50;

user_query: give me a analytical summary about my employees
sql_query:
SELECT /*+ MAX_EXECUTION_TIME(30000) */ 
    e.first_name,
    e.last_name,
    d.name AS department,
    AVG(p.client_feedback_score) AS avg_client_feedback_score,
    AVG(e.salary) AS avg_salary,
    COUNT(DISTINCT ep.role) AS num_roles,
    COUNT(DISTINCT e.department_id) AS num_departments
FROM 
    employe e
JOIN 
    departments d ON e.department_id = d.id
LEFT JOIN 
    performance p ON e.id = p.employee_id
LEFT JOIN 
    employee_projects ep ON e.id = ep.employee_id
GROUP BY 
    e.first_name, e.last_name, d.name
ORDER BY 
    avg_client_feedback_score DESC, avg_salary DESC
LIMIT 50;

user_query: Show the top 3 employees by salary in each department.
sql_query:
SELECT /*+ MAX_EXECUTION_TIME(30000) */ ranked.first_name, ranked.last_name, d.name AS department_name, ranked.salary
FROM (
  SELECT e.id, e.first_name, e.last_name, e.department_id, e.salary,
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY e.department_id ORDER BY e.salary DESC) AS salary_rank
  FROM `employe` e
) ranked
JOIN `departments` d ON ranked.department_id = d.id
WHERE ranked.salary_rank <= 3
ORDER BY d.name, ranked.salary_rank
LIMIT 50
